members.name: for
members.description:
Specifier for list of form associated or contentEditable peer elements that 
should partake in forming the URL.

members.name: form
members.description: Directed Scoped Specifier to a form element that we should use to form the url and body from.

members.name: shadow
members.description:
If as=html, specify whether to (stream) the contents into an attached shadow DOM or not.
            Possible values:

            closed\n\ropen\n\r

members.name: target
members.description: Directed Scoped Specifier to the DOM element where the retrieved content should be applied.

members.name: when
members.description: Directed Scoped Specifier to a (button) element, to delay submitting the fetch request until that button is clicked.

members.name: method
members.description:
The http verb to be used for the request
            Possible values:

            DELETE
GET
HEAD
OPTIONS
PATCH
POST
PUT
TRACE

members.name: as
members.description:
Indicates whether to treat the response as HTML or JSON or Text
            Possible values:

            html\n\rjson\n\rtext\n\r

members.name: noCache
members.description: Do not cache results even if the url has been invoked before.

members.name: stream
members.description: Stream the contents into the target element
